did.head: Overview of the Collection

did.abstract: The office of the Registrar of Voters was established in the early 1860s. The office is responsible for registering voters, the voting machines, polling place, and absentee balloting.

bioghist.head: History
bioghist.p: The Office of the Registrar of Voters was established in the early 1860s. The Registrar is an elected position. One Democrat and one Republican Registrar is elected to represent their respective party. The office is responsible for registering voters, the voting machines, polling place, and absentee balloting. When voting is complete, the office, in conjunction with a duly appointed moderator, compiles and tallies the votes. Once this has been done, the moderator sends a copy of the results to the Secretary of State and to the Town Clerk.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: The Voter Registration Records contain checklists of voters and voter registration cards from the City of Hartford. The cards contain some or all of the following personal information on registered voters: name, residence (including address changes within the city), caucus and party affiliation, ward number, date individual became eligible to vote, place and date of birth, dates of continuous residence, occupation and employer, sex, marital status, and naturalization data.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Series I: Checklists of Voters (1840-1951) consists of 189 bound volumes. Each volume lists the electors eligible to vote in that election. The lists were prepared by the Registrar of Voters and are organized by ward, precinct, street name (in alphabetical order) and address. The volumes are organized chronologically.

Series II: Hartford Voter Registration Cards (1916-1986) are organized by the date the individual became ineligible to vote; within the “off-dates” the cards are filed alphabetically. The cards include some or all of the following information: name, residence (including address changes within the city), caucus and party affiliation, ward number, date individual became eligible to vote, place and date of birth, dates of continuous residence, occupation and employer, sex, marital status, and naturalization data. The cards are arranged in three alphabetical sequences prior to 1969. The first sequence dates from 1916-66, with bulk dates of 1922-34. The second sequence dates from 1926-1968, with bulk dates of 1935-65. The third sequence is not dated but appears to date from the 1960s. Following these three alphabetical sequences, the cards are arranged alphabetically within each year, 1969-84.

custodhist.head: Custodial History
custodhist.p: The Hartford Voter Registration Records were transferred to Historical Manuscripts and Archives division (now Archives and Special Collections) as part of the Peoples of Connecticut Ethnic Heritage Project in August 1979. Hartford Voter Registration cards from 1981, 1982, and 1983 were transferred to Historical Manuscripts and Archives in January, 1989; cards from 1984 were transferred in June, 1990.
